      <h2>Best Zero Forex Markup Credit Cards in India</h2>
      <p>Every international transaction on a regular credit card incurs a forex markup of 2-3.5% — a hidden charge that most cardholders don't notice until they check their statement. On a ₹50,000 international purchase, this means ₹1,000-₹1,750 extra in charges. Zero forex markup cards eliminate this entirely, converting your foreign currency transactions at the interbank exchange rate with zero additional markup.</p>
      <p>These cards are essential for anyone who regularly spends in foreign currencies — international online shoppers (Amazon US, eBay, Etsy), SaaS subscribers (Adobe, Microsoft, Spotify), frequent international travellers, students paying foreign university fees, or professionals working with global clients. The savings compound significantly over time.</p>

      <h2>Key Features of Zero Forex Cards</h2>
      <ul class="feature-list">
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Absolute Zero Markup:</strong> No hidden currency conversion fee — transactions are settled at the interbank Visa/Mastercard rate</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Works Online & Offline:</strong> Zero markup applies to both physical swipes abroad and online international purchases</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>150+ Currency Support:</strong> Transact in any currency supported by Visa/Mastercard with automatic conversion to INR</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>No Transaction Limits:</strong> Zero markup benefit applies to all international transactions regardless of amount</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Real-Time Rates:</strong> Exchange rate is locked at the exact moment of transaction — no delayed settlement surprises</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Additional Travel Perks:</strong> Many zero forex cards also offer lounge access, travel insurance, and reward points</li>
      </ul>

